docs.lead_paragraph: The price of brand-name prescription medicines is rising far faster than the inflation rate, while the price of generic drugs has plummeted, creating the largest gap so far between the two.

headline.seo: Cost of Brand-Name Prescription Medicines Soaring
headline.main: Brand-Name Drug Prices Rise Sharply, Report Says
headline.print_headline: Brand-Name Drug Prices Rise Sharply, Report Says

docs.abstract: Express Scripts report says price of brand-name prescription medicines is rising far faster than inflation rate, while price of generic drugs has plummeted, creating largest gap so far between the two; brand-name prices rose over 13 percent from September 2011 to September 2012.
docs.snippet: The price of brand-name prescription medicines is rising far faster than the inflation rate, while the price of generic drugs has plummeted, creating the largest gap so far between the two.

docs.lead_paragraph: Leaders of the effort said workers were protesting what they said were low wages and retaliation against several workers who have backed the campaign.

headline.seo: Drive to Unionize Fast-Food Workers Opens in N.Y.
headline.main: In Drive to Unionize, Fast-Food Workers Walk Off the Job
headline.print_headline: Drive to Unionize Fast-Food Workers Begins

docs.abstract: Campaign aims to unionize dozens of fast-food restaurants in New York City in hopes of raising wages to $15 an hour; workplace experts call campaign, backed by community and civil rights groups, largest effort to unionize fast-food employees ever undertaken in the United States; labor union has engaged 40 full-time organizers to enlist workers at McDonald's, Wendys, Domino's, Taco Bell and other restaurants across the city.
docs.snippet: Leaders of the effort said workers were protesting what they said were low wages and retaliation against several workers who have backed the campaign.
